About this item

  • Built-In Bluetooth Speaker: Enjoy crisp, clear audio up to 30 feet away with the Homewerks bath fan, featuring a Bluetooth speaker that seamlessly connects to your smart devices, enhancing your bathroom experience with your favorite tunes.
  • Ultra-Quiet Ventilation: Operating at just 1.5 sones, this bath fan ensures a peaceful environment, delivering the sound level of rustling leaves while efficiently ventilating your bathroom.
  • Powerful Airflow: With a robust 70 CFM, this fan provides a healthy and powerful airflow, perfect for maintaining fresh air in rooms up to 70 square feet, ensuring comfort and hygiene.
  • Easy Installation: The 7.25 x 7.5 inches fan housing size typically requires no cutting or attic access, and the quick connect wiring system allows for faster, hassle-free installation.
  • Durable and Reliable: The AC motor is engineered for continuous operation, ensuring long-lasting performance, making it an ideal choice for consistent, dependable ventilation.
  • BEST USED WITH HOMEWERKS BATH FANS: Compatible with most bathroom ventilation fans with a light. Best used with Homewerks bath fan models: 7150-02 or 7150-03N

Product Description

Transform your room into a serene oasis with the Homewerks Exhaust Fan with Bluetooth Speaker. Designed to blend superior functionality with exceptional sound quality, this innovative fan combines clear audio with a quiet bath fan. Enjoy your favorite tunes or podcasts with Bluetooth connectivity that provides crisp, clear audio up to 30 feet away. Compatible with most smart devices, you can effortlessly stream music, podcasts, and more. Experience the tranquility of a 1.5 sones sound level which is as quiet as rustling leaves. Its ultra-quiet operation ensures your space remains peaceful, while the robust 70 CFM airflow keeps your room fresh and well-ventilated. Perfectly suited for spaces up to 70 square feet, this ventilation fan ensures powerful and healthy airflow for a comfortable environment. Although commonly seen in bathrooms, this fan can also be installed in exercise rooms or laundry rooms or anywhere where humid air needs to be removed. Because this fan is the standard housing size of 7.25 x 7.5 inches, installation typically doesn’t require any cutting or attic access. Simplify your setup with quick connect wiring for faster, hassle-free installation. Engineered with a durable AC motor designed for continuous operation, this Homewerks Bluetooth fan promises consistent performance for years to come. Enjoy the confidence of a 3-year limited warranty on the exhaust fan and a 1-year limited warranty on the Bluetooth speaker. Upgrade to the Homewerks Bath Fan with Bluetooth Speaker and enhance your daily routine with the perfect blend of efficiency and entertainment.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Customers say

Customers find the bath fan's appearance nice and appreciate its fan quality. The sound quality receives mixed feedback, with some saying it's above decent while others find it too loud. The functionality and ease of installation also get mixed reviews, with some saying it works great and is easy to install, while others report issues. Moreover, the Bluetooth functionality is problematic, with one customer reporting that the Bluetooth feature doesn't work at all. Additionally, the light level and speaker quality receive negative feedback, with multiple customers noting there's no light and describing the speaker as low quality.

    1.0 out of 5 stars Installation Nightmare
    Reviewed in the United States on April 21, 2020
    Style: 90 CFM Bluetooth Bath FanVerified Purchase
    UPDATE: After 4 months the bluetooth speaker no longer works. I have followed all of the troubleshooting steps multiple times before deciding to remove it and replace it.
    Picking up something different and hopefully better tomorrow.
    The only good thing about this exhaust fan is the quiet fan and moderate speaker.
    The installation is a nightmare if you are installing into a preexisting location. First and foremost the brackets for this type of unit should be able to be mounted from the top. The short bracket is not long enough to install properly when the preexisting cutout edge is flush to the stud. It barely reaches the adjacent stud and is past the placement for the support screw so it wobbles. Had to drill a screw into the bracket to stabilize it.
    The bracket on the other side could be barely reached because that side of the fan location is too close to the pitch of the roof.
    This is why a top mounting bracket would have been preferred. Because of the location, I was not comfortable with its stability so I added my own additional support.
    I am not returning the fan because I have no desire to spend another hour and a half in my attic.
    This should have taken me 20 minutes tops.
    Coming from a licensed Electrician I have to say this is hands down the worse installation design I've put my hands on. Thankfully it is in my own home because I would have ripped it out in a customers home. I can live with it.
